        <div class="row features small-up-1 medium-up-3">
          <div class="column text-center">
            <h4 class="font-color-dark">Flexible + Performant</h4>
            <p class="font-color-dark">Leaf aims to be a flexible Machine
            Learning Framework while maintaining unachieved performance. Minimal
            dependencies and engineering Leaf from the ground up brings
            Leaf close to optimal efficicency. While you can flexible build
            complex machine learning models through composing layers. We
            designed Leaf and other projects to be as modular as possible, which
            means you can bring in new functionality through plugins others
            provide and are able to easily extend Leaf and the ecosystem.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="column text-center">
            <h4 class="font-color-dark">Efficient + Scaleable</h4>
            <p class="font-color-dark">
              Leaf is truely portable and scalebale. We designed Leaf, so that
              you can deploy your networks on various machines and platforms.
              Test your network on your local desktop, train the same network on
              your servers and use the trained network on the smartphones
              of your users. Networks with Leaf efficiently use the availabe
              hardware resources on the machine. No matter if it is a tiny
              memory restricted device or a multi GPU server, you deploy your
              network, Leaf takes care of the rest.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="column text-center">
            <h4 class="font-color-dark">Research + Production</h4>
            <p class="font-color-dark">
              Leaf is made for use in research and production. Researchers gain
              the advantage of an expressive, performant and easy-to-use
              Framework to develop new algorithms. Rust's package manager and
              Leaf's modular design make it easy for researchers to publish their
              work, while companies can access these plugins and use them in
              their own applications. Leaf tries to bring research and production
              closer together. No need to rewrite your network if you want to
              bring it into production.
            </p>
          </div>
